      <context>
         <p>Data source specified in the program header determines the type of transaction data. It can be:</p>
      </context>
      <steps-unordered>
         <li>
            <p>Order line item</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Line item</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Sales line item</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Invoice line item</p>
         </li>
      </steps-unordered>
      <div>
         <p>Not all transaction data loaded in the system is qualified to be used in calculating the qualification amount and benefit amount.</p>
         <p>The following filtering logic applies:</p>
         <ul>
            <li>
               <uicontrol>Filtered by program dates:</uicontrol> If the transaction line is of type Order Line Item, <uicontrol>Pricing Date</uicontrol> of the order line item must fall between the program start date and end date.</li>
            <li>
               <uicontrol>Filtered by filters specified in program scope</uicontrol>
            </li>
            <li>
               <uicontrol>Filtered by-products included and excluded: </uicontrol>
               <ul>
                  <li>If the program definition has categories defined, filtered by products that are part of the category.</li>
                  <li>Filtering logic is independent among programs, which means one transaction line can be potentially bucketed into multiple payout schedules and be counted more than once.</li>
               </ul>
            </li>
         </ul>
         <p>New "Type" field value for the Q&amp;B page_CIM441 (It is applicable for MEB, RSP, PKG, BUNDLE, PRSP) </p>
         <ol>
            <li>Add a new value "Product Group" if the benefit line is for a product group</li>
            <li>Change CPG type to be "CPG". It is "All" in R1.</li>
         </ol>
      </div>
